intro: Sabicea setiloba, commonly known as the slender-stemmed sabicea, is a flowering plant belonging to the legume family, Fabaceae. It is native to tropical regions of Africa, particularly in countries like Kenya and Tanzania. The plant is characterized by its slender, climbing stems and trifoliate leaves with small, rounded leaflets. Its flowers are typically small and clustered, producing a pale yellow to greenish hue. Sabicea setiloba is often found in moist, shaded environments such as forest understories and along stream banks.
